[assistant] Fixed the ordering side effect.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - The new test used `task.invoke()`.
[assistant] - In Netty’s shaded `ForkJoinTask`, `invoke()` can touch `ForkJoinPool.common`, which initializes the common pool before `ForkJoinPoolTest` sets its system properties.
[assistant] - That made `ForkJoinPoolTest` observe the default parallelism (`23`) instead of the configured value (`1`).
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Updated `CountedCompleterAnonymous1Test` to call `task.compute()` directly instead of `task.invoke()`.
[assistant] - This still initializes and exercises `CountedCompleter`, including the active class’s `Unsafe` access path, but avoids initializing `ForkJoinPool.common`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Commit amended:
[assistant] - `b08e253cf8 Add CountedCompleter unsafe access coverage test`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Working tree is clean. Tests were not run.
[assistant-event] text_end
